    {
      "id": "135d18f5_372a6dfe",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/common/certInitializer/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 54,
      "message": "Hmmm I'm trying to figure out how to allow to use it easily without rebuilding all onap charts.\n\nI'm thinking about:\n\nglobal:\n    certInitializer:\n      importCustomCertsEnabled: false\n      customCerts: <config map name>\n\nthe default value for customCerts would be set to the name of configmap that will be created if someone provides .pem file\n\nin this way one can create configmap manually and then just add an override passing its name\nAlternatively if you are rebuilding all onap charts you can easily provide pem file to the directory in certInitializer and get configmap created automatically\n\ndo you think it makes sense?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4965,
        "name": "Krzysztof Opasiak",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "k.opasiak@samsung.com",
        "username": "kopasiak"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-30 15:05:16.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "9deb74fc_31a234a7",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/common/certInitializer/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 8,
      "line": 54,
      "message": "Would you be comfortable with the current state even if it's not the best solution? I think your proposal make sense but resource wise we did not really plan for this to last that long. Maybe we can could create a new JIRA to make this feature not require chart rebuild?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5732,
        "name": "Sebastien Premont-Tendland",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "sebastien.premont@bell.ca",
        "username": "spremont"
      },
      "updated": "2020-07-30 18:11:13.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "135d18f5_372a6dfe",
      "unresolved": true
    },
